Hello everyone, and good evening =97
You are receiving this email because I have agreed to supervise your TIM pr=
oject during the Winter 2026 term for TIMG 5901 (MEng), 5905 (MEnt), 5907 (=
MABA), or 5908 (MDTE).
Welcome aboard =97 I look forward to working with you!
Each supervisor runs their TIM project completion process differently. For =
your course, please follow the schedule and process provided here, and use =
the forms included.
________________________________
DOCUMENTS INCLUDED
I am sending you five documents that will guide our work this term:

  1.
Schedule =96 Winter 2026
This outlines the process we will follow to develop your project. We may ma=
ke small adjustments along the way based on client needs or unforeseen even=
ts.
  2.
Client=96TIM Project Alignment Check
We will use this form to ensure that you, the client, and I all share a cle=
ar and aligned understanding of the project.
  3.
SAR (Student Agreement Request)
You will use this form to secure formal approval for your TIM project.
  4.
TIM Gate 1 Project Template
Use this to prepare your G1 presentation. A final version of your G1 slide =
deck must be submitted to the TIM Office at the end of the Winter term.
  5.
TB Supervisions =96 Winter 2026
A list of the students I am supervising, including pathways, clients, and p=
roject titles.

________________________________
PRIORITIES =97 WHAT TO DO FIRST

  1.
Complete the Client=96TIM Project Alignment Check Form
This is the first and most important step. We must confirm alignment betwee=
n the client, you, and me before moving forward.
  2.
Complete and Sign the SAR
Finalize your SAR only after we confirm alignment with the client. Then sen=
d it to me via email.
  3.
Complete =93TIM Project Report Start=94
This is a required TIMG 5110 assignment and will help you begin your projec=
t report effectively.

________________________________
CLIENT MEETINGS & INTERACTIONS
We will meet and interact with your clients as needed throughout the term. =
Remember that clients do not do your work!
These meetings and interactions ensure that your SAR and project direction =
stay fully aligned with client expectations. Keep in mind that you have two=
 stakeholders to satisfy: your client and your supervisor (me).
________________________________
TIM PTC RESOURCE (PROJECT AND THESIS COMPLETION MODULE)
You will soon have access to TIM Project and Thesis Completion (TIM PTC), t=
he digital resource I use to help students develop strong TIM projects and =
theses. Access will be granted as soon as Fall term students complete their=
 TIM projects.
You will retain access throughout the Winter term.
How to Access TIM PTC

  1.
Log into Brightspace.
  2.
Select =93Resource.=94
  3.
Choose TIM Project and Thesis Completion.

Inside TIM PTC, you can:

  *
Follow the full project schedule.
  *
Upload all six report deliverables and your G1 slide decks.
  *
Review recently completed TIM projects.
  *
Access detailed guidelines for every chapter of your report.
  *
Use curated ChatGPT prompts to support your work.
  *
And much more.

To get started, please review the module titled:
=93Schedule, Portals to Upload Deliverables, and Other Project Essentials.=
=94
Please let me know immediately if you encounter issues/errors on the TIM PT=
C pages or have suggestions on how to improve them. I will fix or improve t=
he resource quickly.
________________________________
I=92m excited to work with each of you this Winter and to support you in pr=
oducing excellent TIM project reports.
Once again =97 welcome aboard!
Warm regards,
Tony B.


